							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Megilat Ester </title>
							<title xml:lang="he">מגלת אסתר</title>
							<note>
								<p>Preceded by three benedictions, and followed by one benediction. </p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Leather scroll of the 16th to 17th century. </p>
						<objectDesc form="scroll ">
							<supportDesc material="leather">
								<support>Leather. </support>
								<extent>6 membranes, 20 columns. <dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>162/308</height>
										<width>2810</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<collation>
									<p>6 membranes, with ivory roller, mounted with brass. </p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>A few scrapes/delaminations on leather writing surface. </p>
									<p>Substantial and deliberate fold between each text column. </p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="20" ruledLines="21" writtenLines="21">
									<p>Uniform layout. </p>
									<p>Ruling by hard point,
membrane by membrane.</p>
									<p>Visible pricking. </p>
									<p>Hair side and flesh side of membranes distinguishable. </p>
									<p>Three tagin on שעטנזגץ and one on בדהחיק. The letter ח is arched throughout. </p>
									<p>A few majuscular or minuscular letters. </p>
									<p>The names of the sons of Haman arranged in 11 lines, in accordance with the rule. </p>
									<p>Ivory roller (308mm high). Roller handle has brass ferrule. Wooden core. </p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
